explanation:
1 revolution = 360° = 2π rad.
Therefore: 2 rev = 720° = 4π rad;
45° = 1/8 rev = π/4 rad;
π/2 rad = 90° = 1/4 rev.

Kepler's laws are: 1) planets move in elliptical orbits with the Sun at one focus;
2) the line joining a planet and the Sun sweeps equal areas in equal times;
3) the square of the orbital period is proportional to the cube of the semi-major axis.
